'''文化组学'''（{{lang-en|culturomics}}）是指通过电子化文本的量化分析研究人类行为与文化趋势的{{link-en|计算词典学|computational lexicology}}方法。<ref>{{cite news | first=Patricia | last=Cohen | title=In 500 Billion Words, New Window on Culture | newspaper=New York Times | url=http://www.nytimes.com/2010/12/17/books/17words.html | date=16 December 2010 | accessdate=2016-10-16 | archive-date=2021-02-13 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210213215253/http://www.nytimes.com/2010/12/17/books/17words.html | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|first=Brian|last=Hayes|url=http://www.americanscientist.org/issues/id.12418,y.2011,no.3,content.true,page.1,css.print/issue.aspx|title=Bit Lit|journal=American Scientist|volume=99|issue=3|page=190|doi=10.1511/2011.90.190|date=May–June 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161018204747/http://www.americanscientist.org/issues/id.12418,y.2011,no.3,content.true,page.1,css.print/issue.aspx|archivedate=2016-10-18}}</ref>研究者对海量数字档案进行[[数据挖掘|数据挖掘]]以研究人们使用的语言与词汇，进而揭示其中反应出来的文化现象。<ref>{{cite journal | url=http://www.amhighed.com/documents/charleston2011/AIHE2011_Proceedings.pdf#page=228 | first=David W. | last=Letcher | title=Cultoromics: A New Way to See Temporal Changes in the Prevalence of Words and Phrases | journal=American Institute of Higher Education 6th International Conference Proceedings | volume=4 | issue=1 | page=228 | date=April 6, 2011 | author= | access-date=2016-10-16 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303215026/http://www.amhighed.com/documents/charleston2011/AIHE2011_Proceedings.pdf#page=228 | archive-date=2016-03-03 | dead-url=yes }}</ref>“文化组学”一词是2010年创造的[[新词|新词]]，由英文中的“文化”（{{lang|en|culture}}）与“[[组学|组学]]”（{{lang|en|omics}}）二词合并而成，当年《[[自然_(期刊)|自然]]》上发表的《通过海量电子化书籍对文化进行量化分析》（''Quantitative Analysis of Culture Using Millions of Digitized Books''）一文首次提出了该词。论文的作者为[[哈佛大学|哈佛大学]]学者让-巴蒂斯特·米歇尔（Jean-Baptiste Michel）与埃雷兹·利柏曼·埃登（Erez Lieberman Aiden）。<ref>{{cite journal | first1=Jean-Baptiste | last1=Michel | first2=Erez | last2=Liberman Aiden | title=Quantitative Analysis of Culture Using Millions of Digitized Books | journal=Science | date=16 December 2010 | url=http://www.sciencemag.org/content/early/2010/12/15/science.1199644 | doi=10.1126/science.1199644 | pmid=21163965 | volume=331 | issue=6014 | pmc=3279742 | pages=176–82 | access-date=2016-10-16 | archive-date=2012-04-24 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120424211742/http://www.sciencemag.org/content/early/2010/12/15/science.1199644 | dead-url=no }}</ref>

米歇尔与埃登还参与了[[Google实验室|Google实验室]]的项目{{link-en|Google Ngram Viewer|Google Ngram Viewer}}。这个项目通过[[n元语法|n元语法]]（n-gram）分析[[Google图书|Google图书]]中的数据，以展示语言中的文化模式随时间的变化。

